The paper focuses on combining Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and a state of the art dense Simultaneous Localisation and Mapping (SLAM) system for 3D semantic mapping. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as semantic segmentation and SLAM, which are commonly found in the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of this system for mobile robots, which falls under the cs.RO sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as CNNs, which are commonly found in the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of probabilistic fusion, which is a technique commonly used in the cs.GR sub-category.
